  "message": "fix(js): use ast-grep for var declaration finding display\n\nSame bug pattern as fixed in aa834ee for division detection:\nThe count used ast-grep's semantic 'var $X' pattern, but display\nalways used a regex that could show incorrect examples.\n\nNow mirrors the debugger/NaN detection pattern:\n- When ast-grep is available: use show_ast_detailed_patterns with 'var $X'\n- When unavailable: fall back to the regex pattern\n\n\ud83e\udd16 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.5 <noreply@anthropic.com>",
